Ughelli- HRM S.P. Luke, Kalanama the Viii (JP) Ogiame, Pere of Akugbene Mein Kingdom has awarded scholarship to 48 students from public secondary schools in Bomadi Local Government Area of Delta State. Kalanama the Viii speaking at the occasion of Akugbene Christian Fellowship, ACF, in conjunction with Akugbene Mein Kingdom at his palace in the ancient town of Akugbene disclosed through the co-ordinator of the scholarship programmme Mr. Flemming Carter that the recipients were drawn from public secondary schools and are from the 12 communities that make up the Council Area. He further stated that the scholarship programme started in 2012 and have awarded scholarship to 100 students from public secondary schools in his domain. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCEÂ DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! While emphasising the need for students to take their studies seriously added that, the recipients of the scholarship scheme for the 2020/2021 academic session were based on merit. The monarch in his earlier thanksgiving at the occasion thanked God for making him more than a conqueror and appreciated Governor Ifeanyi Okowa of Delta State for the robust relationship he has with him. Unjustly Dismissed Capt. Monye, Who Served Three Heads Of State, Turns Beggar FG, Lawmaker Train 150 Youths ln Telfairia, Tomato Production Kalanama the Viii also commended his palace chiefs for their prayers and support and promised to sustained the monthly stipend of 5,000 thousand naira for the oldest man and woman in the 12 communities in his domain. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION